laboratory_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis; 1.4 cm metallic density structure at the right lung base; region of peripheral hyperenhancement in hepatic segment 6 measuring 3.2 x 2.1 cm; kidneys of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram; multiple bilateral renal hypodensities, the largest measuring 1.3 cm; appendix is fluid-filled and dilated, measuring up to 9 mm in diameter with wall hyperenhancement; no evidence of perforation or abscess.
